The paper deals with adversarial attacks on neural networks in computer vision, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The use of regularization techniques also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses security threats and defense mechanisms, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The use of neural networks and optimization techniques suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) categories.
